Rinse the @quinoa{½%cup} under running water for at least ~{30%seconds} (this is very important to improve flavour!). Boil a #medium-sized pot{} of water (around 1 1/2l) with half the @vegetable stock pot{½}. Boil the quinoa for ~{8%minutes} then drain. Put back in the empty pot and cover with a #tea towel{}.

Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop a third of the red pepper into tiny ½cm squares. Chop the remainder into roughly 1cm squares. Chop the @vine tomatoes{2} into 1cm cubes. Peel and very finely chop the @red onion{½}(peeled and finely chopped).

Wrap the @almonds{2} in a clean tea towel or between #clingfilm{} and whack them with the bottom of a #saucepan{} to lightly crush them. Drain and thoroughly rinse the @organic lentils{1%can}.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @diced chorizo{1} and cook for a few mins until it just turns crispy at the edges. Remove from the pan but leave any juices in the pan.

Turn the heat to medium and add the red onion and the larger red pepper squares (we'll use the small ½cm squares at the end). Cook for ~{7%minutes} until soft.

Once the ingredients have softened up, add the tomato and chorizo and cook for another few mins before tipping in the lentils and stirring everything together.

Remove the pan from the heat and stir through @coriander{2%tbsp}(chopped), the quinoa, the small squares of raw red pepper, almonds and finish off by crumbling over the @feta cheese{1%cup}(crumbled using your hands).

> Rumour has it that Superman's powers don't actually come from the Planet Krypton. They're from this dinner. Quinoa is a complete protein (which means it contains all essential nine amino acids we need to be at our best), whilst almonds and feta give you another protein hit together with a dose of magnesium, vitamin B and vitamin E. Who needs supplements when you're eating this well?!